Isn't that your bullshit saying?

74
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,810
Hey, hey! Hey! Don't walk away from me!

75
00:06:00,980 --> 00:06:03,440
Where'd you go
on your little field trip, huh?

76
00:06:04,190 --> 00:06:05,190
Where?

77
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:08,740
Did you go see Mike?

78
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:10,660
He didn't see me.

79
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:15,200
Yeah, well, that mother and her daughter
did and they called the cops.

80
00:06:15,290 --> 00:06:18,500
Now, did anyone else see you?

81
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:20,420
Anyone at all?

82
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:22,250
Come on, I need you to think!

83
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:24,420
Nobody saw me!

84
00:06:25,710 --> 00:06:27,380
You put us in danger.

85
00:06:28,300 --> 00:06:29,760
You realize that, right?

86
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,970
You promised...

87
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:35,010
I go!

88
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:36,720
And I never leave!

89
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,020
Nothing ever happens!

90
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:42,440
Yeah! Nothing happens and you stay safe!

91
00:06:45,190 --> 00:06:46,400
You lie!

92
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:50,360
I don't lie!
I protect and I feed and I teach!

93
00:06:50,450 --> 00:06:54,830
And all I ask of you is
that you follow three simple rules.

94
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:56,990
Three rules. And you know what?

95
00:06:58,250 --> 00:07:00,210
You can't even do that!

96
00:07:04,790 --> 00:07:06,050
<font color="#ff00ff">[bangs]</font>

97
00:07:06,130 --> 00:07:07,130
You're grounded.

98
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:09,630
You know what that means?

99
00:07:10,340 --> 00:07:12,430
It means no Eggos...

100
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:18,140
And no TV for a week.

101
00:07:24,610 --> 00:07:26,770
All right, knock it off. Let go.

102
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:29,990
<font color="#ff00ff">[grunts]</font>

103
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:31,900
Okay.

104
00:07:31,990 --> 00:07:33,570
Two weeks.

105
00:07:35,030 --> 00:07:36,280
Let go!

106
00:07:37,740 --> 00:07:39,870
- A month!
- No!

107
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,080
Well, congratulations.

108
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:48,210
You just graduated from no TV for a month
to no TV at all!

109
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,590
No!

110
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:53,260
No! No. No!

111
00:07:53,340 --> 00:07:57,890
You have got to understand that
there are consequences to your actions.

112
00:07:57,970 --> 00:07:59,930
You are like Papa!

113
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:01,230
Really?

114
00:08:01,890 --> 00:08:04,020
I'm like that psychotic son of a bitch?

115
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:07,150
Wow! All right.
You wanna go back in the lab?

116
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:09,610
One phone call. I can make that happen.

117
00:08:09,690 --> 00:08:11,240
I hate you.

118
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:13,240
Yeah, well,
I'm not so crazy about you, either.

119
00:08:13,320 --> 00:08:15,110
You know why? 'Cause you're a brat.

120
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:16,450
You know what that word means?

121
00:08:16,530 --> 00:08:19,580
How about that be your word
for the day, huh? Brat.

122
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:22,710
Why don't we look it up? B-R-A-T.

123
00:08:22,790 --> 00:08:23,790
Brat.

124
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:30,300
Hey! What the hell is wrong with you?

125
00:08:31,550 --> 00:08:33,840
<font color="#ff00ff">[grunts]</font> Hey!

126
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,140
Hey!

127
00:08:36,970 --> 00:08:38,390
Hey! Hey!

128
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:42,020
Open this door!

129
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:44,020
Open the damn door!

130
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,730
You wanna go out in the world?

131
00:08:45,810 --> 00:08:47,400
You better grow up!

132
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:49,270
Grow the hell up!

133
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,440
<font color="#ff00ff">[screams]</font>

134
00:08:57,950 --> 00:08:59,200
<font color="#ff00ff">[sobbing]</font>

135
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:15,090
Mom?

136
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:18,590
Will?

137
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,390
Hello?

138
00:10:01,970 --> 00:10:03,640
<font color="#ff00ff">[Mike]</font> Do you like those grapes, Holly?

139
00:10:04,770 --> 00:10:07,770
Hey, Mom, I was thinking about
staying the night at Stacey's tonight?

140
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:09,480
We were gonna have a girl's night.

141
00:10:09,560 --> 00:10:12,270
Romantic comedies, do our nails, gossip...

142
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:14,190
Sure! That sounds like fun.

143
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:18,070
- <font color="#ff00ff">[TV playing indistinctly]</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">[Nancy]</font> Toast? No?

144
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,290
- Hey.
- Hey.

145
00:10:32,420 --> 00:10:33,790
Did you see your mom?

146
00:10:33,880 --> 00:10:36,550
No, she was sleeping. But I left a note.

147
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:41,300
You don't have to do this, you know.

148
00:10:41,970 --> 00:10:43,180
Stop saying that.

149
00:10:52,810 --> 00:10:54,610
- <font color="#ff00ff">[line ringing]</font>
- <font color="#ff00ff">[sighs]</font>

