- <font color="#ff00ff">[Florence]</font> Hawkins Police.
- Flo, it's Joyce again.

151
00:10:58,570 --> 00:11:00,570
Oh, hi, Joyce.
Listen, I gave him your message...

152
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,370
- He's still not there?
- No, but...

153
00:11:02,450 --> 00:11:05,120
Did he get any of my messages
from yesterday? Did you give...

154
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:08,660
- Yes, do you wanna talk to...
- No, no, I need Hopper.

155
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:13,170
Just tell him to call me
the second he gets in. Please.

156
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,960
- Thank you.
- Bye.

157
00:11:16,130 --> 00:11:17,300
<font color="#ff00ff">[sighs]</font>

158
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:22,550
Hey. How you feeling, sleepyhead?

159
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:24,050
- Any better?
- Mmm-mmm.

160
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:26,390
Same as last night? Still weird?

161
00:11:26,470 --> 00:11:27,560
Yeah.

162
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,310
All right. <font color="#ff00ff">[sighs]</font>

163
00:11:30,560 --> 00:11:31,560
Hmm.

164
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,070
Okay, let me see.

165
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:46,830
Is it a fever?

166
00:11:46,870 --> 00:11:51,040
No. Uh, actually, it's cold.

167
00:11:51,120 --> 00:11:52,420
Do you feel cold?

168
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:56,130
No. Just a little out of it.

169
00:11:56,210 --> 00:11:58,630
Like I haven't really woken up yet.

170
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:02,010
You promised no doctor.

171
00:12:02,090 --> 00:12:04,050
And I meant it. No doctor.

172
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,720
You know what?

173
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:08,220
I'm gonna run you a nice bath
and it'll warm you up

174
00:12:08,310 --> 00:12:09,890
and hopefully get you feeling better.

175
00:12:09,970 --> 00:12:12,020
How's that sound? Okay.

176
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:28,740
Morning, Dart.

177
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:31,410
Got you some breakfast.

178
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,870
Your favorite.

179
00:12:36,670 --> 00:12:38,000
I gotta go to school,

180
00:12:38,090 --> 00:12:40,170
but I'll be back soon. Sound good?

181
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:41,710
<font color="#ff00ff">[chitters]</font>

182
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,530
<font color="#ff00ff">[Mike]</font> Stop being a baby
and do it already!

183
00:13:02,610 --> 00:13:05,070
<font color="#ff00ff">[Max]</font> This is so disgusting.
Is this really necessary?

184
00:13:07,700 --> 00:13:08,910
What the hell's going on?

185
00:13:08,990 --> 00:13:11,120
What do you think? We're looking for Dart.

186
00:13:11,740 --> 00:13:12,750
- Jesus!
- <font color="#ff00ff">[Max]</font> Oh!

187
00:13:12,830 --> 00:13:14,040
<font color="#ff00ff">[Mike]</font> Ugh!

188
00:13:14,620 --> 00:13:15,710
<font color="#ff00ff">[grunts]</font>

189
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:17,370
<font color="#ff00ff">[Lucas]</font> Well, well, well.

190
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:19,750
Look who finally decided to show up.

191
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,670
After I drew the short straw.
Real convenient.

192
00:13:23,340 --> 00:13:24,670
You stink!

193
00:13:28,390 --> 00:13:29,390
Hi, Max.

194
00:13:30,220 --> 00:13:31,220
Hi.

195
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,680
- Where's Will?
- He'll be here.

196
00:13:34,770 --> 00:13:36,480
Are you just gonna stand there?

197
00:13:36,890 --> 00:13:38,230
Or you gonna help?

198
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,570
<font color="#ff00ff">[Mr. Clarke]</font> All living things,
from complex mammals

199
00:13:45,650 --> 00:13:48,820
to single-celled organisms,
instinctively respond to danger.

200
00:13:49,490 --> 00:13:52,870
Expose a bacterium to a toxic chemical,
and it will flee.

201
00:13:52,950 --> 00:13:55,540
Or deploy some other defense mechanism.

202
00:13:57,330 --> 00:13:59,040
We're very much the same.

203
00:14:01,090 --> 00:14:04,510
When we encounter danger,
our hearts start pounding.

204
00:14:05,590 --> 00:14:06,590
<font color="#ff00ff">[water dripping]</font>

205
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:11,720
Our palms start to sweat.

206
00:14:14,770 --> 00:14:20,060
These are the signs of the physical
and emotional state we call...

207
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,520
fear.

208
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:29,100
<font color="#ff00ff">[Hopper]</font> Hey, you reached Jim.

209
00:14:29,150 --> 00:14:32,160
I'm probably doing something
incredible right now and I can't...

210
00:14:32,990 --> 00:14:34,200
Mom.

211
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,000
Yeah, sweetie, what is it?

212
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,330
It's too hot.

213
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:48,630
<font color="#ff00ff">[sighs]</font> I... I can cool it down
a little bit, baby,

214
00:14:48,720 --> 00:14:50,930
- but we gotta get your body temp back up.
- No.

215
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:53,720
What?

216
00:14:55,470 --> 00:14:56,770
He likes it cold.

217
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:24,290
Hey, kid.

218
00:15:31,590 --> 00:15:32,800
Listen, um...

219
00:15:34,640 --> 00:15:36,720
about last night, I, uh...

220
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,060
I want this place cleaned up
by the time I get back

221
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:47,360
and then maybe I'll consider
fixing the TV.

222
00:15:47,440 --> 00:15:48,650
You hear me?

223
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:54,450
<font color="#ff00ff">[door opens and closes]</font>

224
00:15:56,950 --> 00:15:58,620
<font color="#ff00ff">[Florence on radio]</font> Come in, Hop.

225
00:16:00,250 --> 00:16:01,460
Come in, Hop.

226
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,170
Come in, Hop.

227
00:16:04,710 --> 00:16:07,500
<font color="#ff00ff">[grunts softly]</font> Yeah.
Yeah, I'm on my way in,

228
00:16:07,590 --> 00:16:10,340
and, yes, I do know what time it is.

229
00:16:11,090 --> 00:16:14,840
Joyce Byers has called
eight times already this morning.

230
00:16:14,930 --> 00:16:16,470
Eight times.

231
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:19,890
For my sake, please deal with her!

232
00:16:24,100 --> 00:16:25,100
<font color="#ff00ff">[whistle blows]</font>

233
00:16:25,150 --> 00:16:28,730
<font color="#ff00ff">[coach]</font> Let's go. Pass it up now.
Get open!

234
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:33,200
<font color="#ff00ff">[laughs]</font> All right! All right, all right!

235
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:35,660
King Steve. King Steve, everyone.

236
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:37,570
I like it. Playing tough today.

237
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:39,330
Jesus! Do you ever stop talking?
Come on!

238
00:16:39,410 --> 00:16:40,950
<font color="#ff00ff">[laughs]</font> What?

239
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,710
You afraid the coach is gonna
bench you now that I'm here? Huh?

240
00:16:44,250 --> 00:16:45,710
<font color="#ff00ff">[grunts]</font>

241
00:16:52,340 --> 00:16:53,630
You were moving your feet.

242
00:16:53,720 --> 00:16:56,970
Plant them next time, draw a charge.

243
00:16:59,970 --> 00:17:01,520
<font color="#ff00ff">[whistle blows]</font>

244
00:17:04,730 --> 00:17:05,940
<font color="#ff00ff">[sniffing]</font>

245
00:17:08,190 --> 00:17:10,070
Don't sweat it, Harrington.

246
